quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  20,13,"And I have chosen you, so listen to what is revealed:"
  20,14,"Surely, I AM ALLAH. There is no god but I, so worship Me and establish Salah for My remembrance."
  20,15,"Surely, the Hour has to come. I would keep it secret so that everyone is given a return for the effort one makes."
  20,16,"So the one who does not believe in it and follows his desires must not make you neglectful of it, otherwise you will perish."
  20,17,"And what is that in your right hand, 0 Musa?""
  20,18,"He said, "It is my staff. I lean on it, and with it I beat down leaves for my sheep, and for me it has many other uses.""
  20,19,"He said, 'Throw it down 0 Musa'."
  20,20,"So, he threw it down, and suddenly it was a snake, running."
  20,21,"He said, "Pick it up and be not scared. We shall restore it to its former state."
  20,22,"And put your hand under your arm and it will come out white, without any disease as another sign,"
  20,23,"so that We may show you some of Our great signs."
  20,24,"Go to the Pharaoh. He has really transgressed.""
  20,25,"He said, "My Lord, put my heart at peace for me"
  20,26,"and make my task easy for me"
  20,27,"and remove the knot from my tongue,"
  20,28,"that they may understand my speech."
  20,29,"And make for me an assistant from my own family:"
  20,30,"Harun, my brother."
  20,31,"Enhance with him-my strength,"
  20,32,"and make him share my task,"
  20,33,"so that we proclaim Your purity a lot"
  20,34,"and remember You a lot."
  20,35,"-You are certainly watchful over us.""
  20,36,"He said, "You have been granted your request 0 Musa."
  20,37,"And We have bestowed Our favour on you once more,"